Nigeria slows petrol imports - agency . Nigeria has slowed its importation of petroleum products , the national news agency reported on Friday . The News Agency of Nigeria said port statistics showed that one vessel carrying 28 , 420 tonnes of petrol was expected to berth in Lagos by Tuesday , while another with 27 , 579 tonnes was also waiting to berth . " The figure is a marked decrease from previous weeks when the number of tankers declared at the port was much higher , " the agency said . It did not give figures for previous weeks . Nigeria pumps over two million barrels of crude oil per day , but its four refineries are plagued by technical problems , limiting their output far below their capacity of 445 , 000 bpd . As a result Nigeria has been importing petrol to minimise shortages . - - Lagos newsroom + 234 1 2630317 
